cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.IT, cs.SI 

This paper deals with privacy in location-based services, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also proposes a differential privacy framework, which involves statistical learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB). The use of Gaussian process conditional priors suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper deals with preserving privacy in a trace, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
